block content
  h2 Sudo &amp; Root User
  p Some files on a computer are critical to system funcationality and therefore it is risky to enable any user to edit them or even remove them.  The root user is the user with all the privileges on the system and the sudo command allows a normal user to temporarily gain elevated permissions like the root user has. Let's learn more

  h2 Video - 9 min
  p
